1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,543
One man sold a secret way

2
00:00:01,610 --> 00:00:03,647
into America's best universities.

3
00:00:03,714 --> 00:00:04,886
Not the front door.

4
00:00:04,953 --> 00:00:06,064
Not the back door.

5
00:00:06,131 --> 00:00:07,365
A side door — and it

6
00:00:07,432 --> 00:00:09,654
cost millions, until the morning the

7
00:00:09,721 --> 00:00:10,721
FBI knocked.

8
00:00:13,189 --> 00:00:14,856
There are, a man named Rick

9
00:00:14,922 --> 00:00:16,774
Singer used to say, three ways

10
00:00:16,841 --> 00:00:18,754
into an elite American college.

11
00:00:18,995 --> 00:00:20,723
The first is the front door.

12
00:00:20,790 --> 00:00:22,333
You earn it — the grades,

13
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:24,190
the scores, the years of work

14
00:00:24,257 --> 00:00:25,738
— and then you take your

15
00:00:25,805 --> 00:00:27,904
chances with everyone else who did

16
00:00:27,970 --> 00:00:29,328
the same. No promises.

17
00:00:29,395 --> 00:00:31,555
That uncertainty is the whole idea.

18
00:00:31,622 --> 00:00:33,351
The second is the back door.

19
00:00:33,417 --> 00:00:35,084
You give the school a great

20
00:00:35,151 --> 00:00:36,817
deal of money — a building,

21
00:00:36,884 --> 00:00:38,304
a wing, a fortune — and

22
00:00:38,370 --> 00:00:40,901
the university, grateful, takes a longer,

23
00:00:40,968 --> 00:00:42,573
warmer look at your child.

24
00:00:42,639 --> 00:00:44,183
A lot of people find that

25
00:00:44,249 --> 00:00:45,916
offensive. But it is legal,

26
00:00:45,983 --> 00:00:47,464
and it is older than any

27
00:00:47,531 --> 00:00:48,531
of us.

28
00:00:48,719 --> 00:00:50,447
And then there was the third

29
00:00:50,514 --> 00:00:52,675
door. The one Singer built himself.

30
00:00:52,741 --> 00:00:54,408
He called it the side door.

31
00:00:54,475 --> 00:00:56,203
It was quieter than the back

32
00:00:56,270 --> 00:00:57,936
door, and far cheaper — and

33
00:00:58,003 --> 00:00:59,793
unlike the other two, it came

34
00:00:59,860 --> 00:01:01,897
with something no honest path can

35
00:01:01,963 --> 00:01:03,568
ever promise. A guarantee.

36
00:01:05,161 --> 00:01:07,260
For roughly eight years, that side

37
00:01:07,326 --> 00:01:08,326
door stood open.

38
00:01:08,393 --> 00:01:10,430
Wealthy parents paid Singer about

39
00:01:10,497 --> 00:01:13,028
twenty-five million dollars to walk their

40
00:01:13,094 --> 00:01:14,946
children through it — past the

41
00:01:15,013 --> 00:01:17,173
admissions officers, past the other

42
00:01:17,240 --> 00:01:19,833
applicants, straight into schools they had

43
00:01:19,899 --> 00:01:21,442
no business getting into.

44
00:01:21,509 --> 00:01:22,991
This is the story of how

45
00:01:23,057 --> 00:01:24,662
that door actually worked.

46
00:01:24,729 --> 00:01:26,457
How a fake athlete was built

47
00:01:26,524 --> 00:01:28,252
out of nothing but paper and

48
00:01:28,319 --> 00:01:30,233
nerve. How a perfect test score

49
00:01:30,299 --> 00:01:32,213
could be manufactured in a room

50
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:33,884
the student barely sat in.

51
00:01:33,951 --> 00:01:36,112
And how the whole machine collapsed

52
00:01:36,178 --> 00:01:37,907
on a single morning in 2019,

53
00:01:37,973 --> 00:01:40,072
when fifty people were arrested at

54
00:01:40,139 --> 00:01:42,114
once, and the country was handed

55
00:01:42,181 --> 00:01:43,847
a brand-new name for a very

56
00:01:43,914 --> 00:01:45,581
old suspicion — that at the

57
00:01:45,647 --> 00:01:47,438
very top, the game is rigged.

58
00:01:47,504 --> 00:01:49,850
Because this story did something rare.

59
00:01:49,917 --> 00:01:51,830
It took a suspicion millions of

60
00:01:51,897 --> 00:01:53,996
people quietly carry — that effort

61
00:01:54,062 --> 00:01:55,852
is not really the currency at

62
00:01:55,919 --> 00:01:57,462
the top — and it produced

63
00:01:57,529 --> 00:01:58,763
the receipts. Names.

64
00:01:58,830 --> 00:02:01,238
Numbers. Recordings. For once, the tilt

65
00:02:01,304 --> 00:02:02,724
in the system was not a

66
00:02:02,791 --> 00:02:04,334
feeling. It was evidence.

67
00:02:04,401 --> 00:02:06,005
It is a story about money.

68
00:02:06,072 --> 00:02:07,862
But underneath, it is about a

69
00:02:07,929 --> 00:02:09,904
question that lives inside every

70
00:02:09,971 --> 00:02:12,563
application, every thick or thin envelope,

71
00:02:12,630 --> 00:02:13,988
every quiet rejection.

72
00:02:14,055 --> 00:02:15,413
What is a place at the

73
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:16,529
top really worth?

74
00:02:16,596 --> 00:02:18,262
And when someone buys one —

75
00:02:18,329 --> 00:02:19,440
who actually pays?

76
00:02:21,372 --> 00:02:23,100
To understand the side door,

77
00:02:23,167 --> 00:02:25,142
you first have to understand the

78
00:02:25,209 --> 00:02:26,382
man standing in it.

79
00:02:26,449 --> 00:02:28,486
William Rick Singer was a college

80
00:02:28,552 --> 00:02:30,281
counselor — but not the kind

81
00:02:30,347 --> 00:02:32,076
who helps polish your essay.

82
00:02:32,142 --> 00:02:34,365
He ran a private counseling business

83
00:02:34,431 --> 00:02:36,407
called The Key, and alongside it

84
00:02:36,473 --> 00:02:38,387
a non-profit, the Key Worldwide

85
00:02:38,453 --> 00:02:40,923
Foundation. On paper, the foundation was

86
00:02:40,989 --> 00:02:43,335
a charity, built to help disadvantaged

87
00:02:43,402 --> 00:02:44,821
kids reach for college.

88
00:02:44,888 --> 00:02:47,110
In reality, prosecutors said, it was

89
00:02:47,177 --> 00:02:48,412
a laundry — a way to

90
00:02:48,478 --> 00:02:50,021
take a bribe and dress it

91
00:02:50,088 --> 00:02:51,199
up as a good deed.

92
00:02:51,329 --> 00:02:53,489
Singer's real talent was never test

93
00:02:53,556 --> 00:02:55,285
prep. It was reading people.

94
00:02:55,351 --> 00:02:57,450
He understood a very specific kind

95
00:02:57,517 --> 00:02:58,813
of fear — the fear of

96
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:00,793
a wealthy parent whose child is

97
00:03:00,860 --> 00:03:02,712
bright, but not extraordinary;

98
00:03:02,778 --> 00:03:04,877
comfortable, but not a sure thing;

99
00:03:04,944 --> 00:03:06,796
good enough for a good school,

100
00:03:06,862 --> 00:03:08,344
but not for the name the

101
00:03:08,410 --> 00:03:10,324
family had been saying out loud

102
00:03:10,391 --> 00:03:11,564
for eighteen years.

103
00:03:11,717 --> 00:03:13,692
That fear is an enormous market.

104
00:03:13,759 --> 00:03:15,364
And Singer met it not with

105
00:03:15,431 --> 00:03:16,727
panic, but with calm.

106
00:03:16,794 --> 00:03:18,398
He would sit a parent down

107
00:03:18,465 --> 00:03:20,317
and explain the doors, the way

108
00:03:20,384 --> 00:03:22,976
a financial advisor explains your options.

109
00:03:23,043 --> 00:03:24,648
The front door, you get in

110
00:03:24,715 --> 00:03:25,715
on your own.

111
00:03:25,781 --> 00:03:27,201
The back door — what he

112
00:03:27,268 --> 00:03:29,737
called institutional advancement — costs

113
00:03:29,803 --> 00:03:31,470
ten times as much, and even

114
00:03:31,537 --> 00:03:33,203
then, no one can promise it

115
00:03:33,270 --> 00:03:34,270
works.

116
00:03:35,264 --> 00:03:37,239
"And I've created this side door

117
00:03:37,306 --> 00:03:39,034
in," he said on one recorded

118
00:03:39,101 --> 00:03:41,632
call. Because, he explained, his families

119
00:03:41,699 --> 00:03:42,871
wanted a guarantee.

120
00:03:42,938 --> 00:03:44,420
Sit with that word for a

121
00:03:44,486 --> 00:03:46,832
moment. Guarantee. Because that single

122
00:03:46,899 --> 00:03:48,442
word is the entire crime.

123
00:03:48,508 --> 00:03:50,978
In honest admissions, nobody can promise

124
00:03:51,044 --> 00:03:52,587
an outcome — not a coach,

125
00:03:52,654 --> 00:03:54,259
not a dean, not a senator.

126
00:03:54,326 --> 00:03:56,116
A guarantee can only exist if

127
00:03:56,183 --> 00:03:58,096
the decision is no longer being

128
00:03:58,163 --> 00:03:59,706
made honestly — if it has

129
00:03:59,773 --> 00:04:01,995
already, quietly, been bought before

130
00:04:02,062 --> 00:04:04,284
anyone in the admissions office ever

131
00:04:04,350 --> 00:04:05,350
opens the file.

132
00:04:07,031 --> 00:04:08,821
And Singer did not advertise.

133
00:04:08,888 --> 00:04:09,999
He didn't need to.

134
00:04:10,066 --> 00:04:11,856
His clients found him the way

135
00:04:11,922 --> 00:04:14,021
the very wealthy find everything —

136
00:04:14,088 --> 00:04:15,878
by word of mouth, one anxious

137
00:04:15,945 --> 00:04:18,043
parent quietly asking another at a

138
00:04:18,110 --> 00:04:20,394
fundraiser, a dinner, the sideline of

139
00:04:20,461 --> 00:04:21,461
a youth game.

140
00:04:21,527 --> 00:04:23,256
That privacy was part of the

141
00:04:23,322 --> 00:04:25,359
product. You were not just buying

142
00:04:25,426 --> 00:04:27,216
a service. You were joining a

143
00:04:27,283 --> 00:04:29,382
circle that already knew the rules

144
00:04:29,448 --> 00:04:30,991
came in a secret edition.

145
00:04:31,058 --> 00:04:33,466
And here is the genuinely uncomfortable

146
00:04:33,532 --> 00:04:35,384
part. Most of what Singer sold

147
00:04:35,451 --> 00:04:36,932
was, technically, legal.

148
00:04:36,999 --> 00:04:39,036
Real counseling. Real essay help.

149
00:04:39,103 --> 00:04:41,695
That ordinary business was the camouflage,

150
00:04:41,762 --> 00:04:43,305
and it is exactly why the

151
00:04:43,372 --> 00:04:44,791
fraud survived so long.

152
00:04:44,858 --> 00:04:47,019
It also let parents tell themselves

153
00:04:47,085 --> 00:04:48,567
a story — that they were

154
00:04:48,633 --> 00:04:51,164
simply being aggressive, devoted parents,

155
00:04:51,231 --> 00:04:52,898
paying for an edge, the way

156
00:04:52,964 --> 00:04:54,322
you pay for a tutor or

157
00:04:54,389 --> 00:04:55,389
a private coach.

158
00:04:55,456 --> 00:04:57,122
The line between that and a

159
00:04:57,189 --> 00:04:58,979
federal crime was a line many

160
00:04:59,046 --> 00:05:00,589
of them chose not to look

161
00:05:00,656 --> 00:05:01,656
at too hard.

162
00:05:03,505 --> 00:05:05,480
Now, the elegant, ugly genius of

163
00:05:05,547 --> 00:05:07,461
it. The money never looked like

164
00:05:07,527 --> 00:05:09,070
a bribe. A parent did not

165
00:05:09,137 --> 00:05:10,557
hand cash to a coach in

166
00:05:10,624 --> 00:05:11,673
a parking garage.

167
00:05:11,740 --> 00:05:13,530
They wrote a generous check —

168
00:05:13,596 --> 00:05:15,078
to a children's charity.

169
00:05:15,145 --> 00:05:16,996
The kind of thing you mention,

170
00:05:17,063 --> 00:05:18,730
lightly, at a dinner party.

171
00:05:18,796 --> 00:05:21,265
Singer's foundation would even mail back

172
00:05:21,332 --> 00:05:23,740
a warm thank-you letter, praising their

173
00:05:23,806 --> 00:05:26,028
generosity, and stating, in writing,

174
00:05:26,095 --> 00:05:27,885
that no goods or services had

175
00:05:27,952 --> 00:05:28,952
been exchanged.

176
00:05:31,092 --> 00:05:32,573
That last line was a lie

177
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:33,640
with a purpose.

178
00:05:33,707 --> 00:05:35,620
Because if no goods or services

179
00:05:35,687 --> 00:05:37,662
were exchanged, the donation was

180
00:05:37,729 --> 00:05:40,198
tax-deductible. So these parents did not

181
00:05:40,265 --> 00:05:42,240
merely buy their child's way in.

182
00:05:42,307 --> 00:05:43,973
They wrote the bribe off on

183
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:46,015
their taxes — and quietly handed

184
00:05:46,082 --> 00:05:47,625
part of the bill to every

185
00:05:47,692 --> 00:05:49,544
other taxpayer in the country.

186
00:05:49,611 --> 00:05:51,648
Fraud, disguised as philanthropy.

187
00:05:51,714 --> 00:05:53,566
Bribery, filed as a deduction.

188
00:05:54,406 --> 00:05:56,011
And this was not a handful

189
00:05:56,078 --> 00:05:57,078
of quiet favors.

190
00:05:57,144 --> 00:05:59,058
It was a business — nationwide,

191
00:05:59,125 --> 00:06:01,038
with a client list, running for

192
00:06:01,105 --> 00:06:02,833
the better part of a decade.

193
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:05,246
Prosecutors traced roughly twenty-five

194
00:06:05,312 --> 00:06:07,658
million dollars flowing to Singer from

195
00:06:07,725 --> 00:06:09,268
parents over those years.

196
00:06:09,334 --> 00:06:11,186
He had built an institution of

197
00:06:11,253 --> 00:06:13,043
his own — a shadow admissions

198
00:06:13,110 --> 00:06:15,332
office, operating in parallel to the

199
00:06:15,399 --> 00:06:17,250
real ones, with its own staff,

200
00:06:17,317 --> 00:06:19,292
its own paperwork, its own price

201
00:06:19,359 --> 00:06:21,581
structure. The genius and the horror

202
00:06:21,648 --> 00:06:23,315
were the same thing: he had

203
00:06:23,381 --> 00:06:24,739
made cheating orderly.

204
00:06:24,806 --> 00:06:26,411
But a guarantee is only as

205
00:06:26,478 --> 00:06:28,391
good as your ability to deliver

206
00:06:28,458 --> 00:06:30,371
it. So Singer built two engines

207
00:06:30,438 --> 00:06:32,722
underneath the charity — two reliable

208
00:06:32,789 --> 00:06:34,579
ways to manufacture a result.

209
00:06:34,646 --> 00:06:35,942
One rigged the tests.

210
00:06:36,008 --> 00:06:38,169
The other invented athletes who did

211
00:06:38,236 --> 00:06:39,236
not exist.

212
00:06:39,302 --> 00:06:40,907
Start with the tests — the

213
00:06:40,974 --> 00:06:41,974
SAT and the ACT.

214
00:06:42,041 --> 00:06:43,769
These are supposed to be the

215
00:06:43,836 --> 00:06:46,058
great equalizer. The same questions,

216
00:06:46,125 --> 00:06:47,915
the same scoring, for the kid

217
00:06:47,981 --> 00:06:49,710
in the gated mansion and the

218
00:06:49,776 --> 00:06:51,752
kid sharing a bedroom with three

219
00:06:51,818 --> 00:06:53,979
siblings. A single number that does

220
00:06:54,046 --> 00:06:55,897
not care who your parents are.

221
00:06:55,964 --> 00:06:58,186
That promise of fairness was exactly

222
00:06:58,253 --> 00:07:00,537
what Singer's first machine was built

223
00:07:00,604 --> 00:07:01,604
to break.

224
00:07:01,670 --> 00:07:02,843
It worked in steps.

225
00:07:02,910 --> 00:07:04,638
And the first step was time.

226
00:07:04,705 --> 00:07:06,557
Singer would coach a family to

227
00:07:06,623 --> 00:07:08,599
get the student extended time on

228
00:07:08,665 --> 00:07:10,702
the exam — the accommodation that

229
00:07:10,769 --> 00:07:12,744
exists for students with genuine

230
00:07:12,811 --> 00:07:15,218
disabilities. To unlock it, prosecutors

231
00:07:15,285 --> 00:07:17,631
said, some families had their children

232
00:07:17,697 --> 00:07:20,043
purport to have a learning disability,

233
00:07:20,110 --> 00:07:22,394
performing just enough to collect the

234
00:07:22,460 --> 00:07:24,868
medical paperwork that bought the extra

235
00:07:24,934 --> 00:07:25,934
hours.

236
00:07:26,001 --> 00:07:27,976
Now stop here, because this part

237
00:07:28,043 --> 00:07:29,339
is easy to get wrong.

238
00:07:29,406 --> 00:07:31,381
Extended time is real, and fair,

239
00:07:31,448 --> 00:07:33,300
and vital for the students who

240
00:07:33,366 --> 00:07:34,416
actually need it.

241
00:07:34,483 --> 00:07:36,828
The scandal is not that accommodations

242
00:07:36,895 --> 00:07:38,994
exist. The scandal is the opposite

243
00:07:39,060 --> 00:07:41,159
— that Singer's families faked the

244
00:07:41,226 --> 00:07:43,139
need, and hijacked a tool built

245
00:07:43,206 --> 00:07:44,996
for the vulnerable to hand an

246
00:07:45,063 --> 00:07:46,791
advantage to the privileged.

247
00:07:46,858 --> 00:07:48,771
The extra time did one specific

248
00:07:48,838 --> 00:07:50,690
thing. It let the student take

249
00:07:50,757 --> 00:07:52,547
the exam alone, on a separate

250
00:07:52,613 --> 00:07:54,650
day, away from the crowded school

251
00:07:54,717 --> 00:07:56,260
gymnasium — at one of two

252
00:07:56,327 --> 00:07:58,920
testing centers Singer quietly controlled.

253
00:07:58,986 --> 00:08:00,715
One was a public high school

254
00:08:00,781 --> 00:08:01,892
in Houston, Texas.

255
00:08:01,959 --> 00:08:03,934
The other, a private school near

256
00:08:04,001 --> 00:08:05,668
West Hollywood, California.

257
00:08:05,734 --> 00:08:07,833
At both places, the person running

258
00:08:07,900 --> 00:08:09,937
the room was on Singer's payroll,

259
00:08:10,004 --> 00:08:12,164
paid somewhere between five and ten

260
00:08:12,231 --> 00:08:13,836
thousand dollars per test.

261
00:08:13,902 --> 00:08:15,692
And once the room belonged to

262
00:08:15,759 --> 00:08:17,734
Singer, the test stopped being a

263
00:08:17,801 --> 00:08:18,801
test.

264
00:08:18,868 --> 00:08:20,473
Meet the second man in the

265
00:08:20,539 --> 00:08:21,897
scheme — Mark Riddell.

266
00:08:21,964 --> 00:08:24,125
Prosecutors did not describe him as

267
00:08:24,191 --> 00:08:25,191
a great teacher.

268
00:08:25,258 --> 00:08:27,604
They described him as something colder

269
00:08:27,670 --> 00:08:29,460
and rarer: a man smart enough

270
00:08:29,527 --> 00:08:31,008
to hit a target score on

271
00:08:31,075 --> 00:08:32,075
demand.

272
00:08:32,142 --> 00:08:34,179
Riddell did not tutor these kids.

273
00:08:34,246 --> 00:08:36,283
He produced their scores himself.

274
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:37,831
In some cases he flew in

275
00:08:37,897 --> 00:08:39,687
and secretly took the exam in

276
00:08:39,754 --> 00:08:41,791
the student's place, using a fake

277
00:08:41,858 --> 00:08:43,957
ID that carried the student's name

278
00:08:44,023 --> 00:08:45,443
and his own photograph.

279
00:08:45,510 --> 00:08:46,991
In other cases he sat in

280
00:08:47,058 --> 00:08:48,601
the room as the proctor —

281
00:08:48,668 --> 00:08:50,520
and after the student had gone

282
00:08:50,586 --> 00:08:52,623
home, he calmly went back through

283
00:08:52,690 --> 00:08:54,789
the answer sheet and corrected the

284
00:08:54,855 --> 00:08:55,855
wrong answers.

285
00:08:55,922 --> 00:08:57,095
And he was careful.

286
00:08:57,162 --> 00:08:58,828
He could land near a chosen

287
00:08:58,895 --> 00:09:00,994
score almost exactly — high enough

288
00:09:01,060 --> 00:09:02,727
to change a future, but not

289
00:09:02,794 --> 00:09:04,275
so high it would trip an

290
00:09:04,342 --> 00:09:05,823
alarm. A believable lie.

291
00:09:05,890 --> 00:09:08,050
Over about eight years, he inflated

292
00:09:08,117 --> 00:09:10,463
scores for twenty-four students across

293
00:09:10,529 --> 00:09:12,752
twenty-seven exams. The parents paid

294
00:09:12,818 --> 00:09:15,041
Singer somewhere between fifteen and

295
00:09:15,107 --> 00:09:17,391
seventy-five thousand dollars a test.

296
00:09:17,458 --> 00:09:19,063
And here is the strangest,

297
00:09:19,129 --> 00:09:21,290
saddest detail. The child often had

298
00:09:21,357 --> 00:09:23,023
no idea. They walked out of

299
00:09:23,090 --> 00:09:25,250
that room believing they had simply

300
00:09:25,317 --> 00:09:26,317
had a good day.

301
00:09:26,384 --> 00:09:28,359
Some of them carried that belief

302
00:09:28,426 --> 00:09:30,031
for years — that the score

303
00:09:30,097 --> 00:09:32,258
was theirs, that the acceptance was

304
00:09:32,325 --> 00:09:34,176
theirs, built a whole sense of

305
00:09:34,243 --> 00:09:36,404
themselves on an achievement that a

306
00:09:36,470 --> 00:09:38,878
stranger had quietly manufactured in an

307
00:09:38,944 --> 00:09:41,166
empty room. The parents thought they

308
00:09:41,233 --> 00:09:43,147
were protecting their children.

309
00:09:43,213 --> 00:09:44,695
In a quiet way, they had

310
00:09:44,762 --> 00:09:46,613
stolen from them the one thing

311
00:09:46,680 --> 00:09:48,285
they most wanted to give —

312
00:09:48,352 --> 00:09:50,142
the right to believe they had

313
00:09:50,208 --> 00:09:51,381
done it themselves.

314
00:09:51,448 --> 00:09:53,176
That was the first machine —

315
00:09:53,243 --> 00:09:54,243
rig the number.

316
00:09:54,310 --> 00:09:56,285
The second was stranger, and far

317
00:09:56,352 --> 00:09:58,204
bolder, because it did not rig

318
00:09:58,270 --> 00:09:59,270
a number at all.

319
00:09:59,337 --> 00:10:00,633
It invented a person.

320
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:03,046
This was Singer's real innovation: the

321
00:10:03,112 --> 00:10:05,705
fake athlete. Elite universities set aside

322
00:10:05,771 --> 00:10:07,932
places for recruited athletes — the

323
00:10:07,999 --> 00:10:09,789
rower, the water polo player,

324
00:10:09,855 --> 00:10:11,646
the sailor, the soccer star —

325
00:10:11,712 --> 00:10:13,626
and they trust their coaches to

326
00:10:13,692 --> 00:10:15,483
fill them. A coach's word can

327
00:10:15,549 --> 00:10:18,080
carry an applicant straight past students

328
00:10:18,147 --> 00:10:19,690
with far stronger grades.

329
00:10:19,757 --> 00:10:22,041
Singer understood the leverage hiding

330
00:10:22,107 --> 00:10:23,218
inside that trust.

331
00:10:23,285 --> 00:10:24,705
If you owned the coach,

332
00:10:24,771 --> 00:10:25,944
you owned the spot.

333
00:10:26,011 --> 00:10:27,863
So his team built athletes out

334
00:10:27,929 --> 00:10:30,090
of paper. They wrote false profiles

335
00:10:30,157 --> 00:10:32,008
— elite club teams the student

336
00:10:32,075 --> 00:10:34,112
had never played for, honors they

337
00:10:34,179 --> 00:10:36,216
had never won, times and rankings

338
00:10:36,283 --> 00:10:37,702
invented from thin air.

339
00:10:37,769 --> 00:10:39,621
When a profile needed a photo,

340
00:10:39,687 --> 00:10:41,971
parents supplied staged ones: a child

341
00:10:42,038 --> 00:10:44,260
posed straining on a rowing machine,

342
00:10:44,327 --> 00:10:45,932
a child standing at a pool

343
00:10:45,999 --> 00:10:47,912
dressed as a water polo player.

344
00:10:47,979 --> 00:10:49,522
And according to the FBI,

345
00:10:49,589 --> 00:10:51,502
in some cases they went further

346
00:10:51,569 --> 00:10:53,729
still — taking the applicant's face

347
00:10:53,796 --> 00:10:55,525
and editing it onto the body

348
00:10:55,591 --> 00:10:57,381
of a real athlete, a stranger

349
00:10:57,448 --> 00:10:59,670
who had actually earned that motion,

350
00:10:59,737 --> 00:11:01,280
that muscle, that moment.

351
00:11:01,347 --> 00:11:03,137
Think about how absurd it had

352
00:11:03,204 --> 00:11:04,808
to get. A teenager who had

353
00:11:04,875 --> 00:11:07,097
never competed was turned, on paper,

354
00:11:07,164 --> 00:11:09,078
into a recruited coxswain — the

355
00:11:09,144 --> 00:11:11,058
person who steers a racing crew

356
00:11:11,125 --> 00:11:12,729
boat and calls the rhythm.

357
00:11:12,796 --> 00:11:14,401
A kid who had never played

358
00:11:14,468 --> 00:11:16,505
water polo was handed a position,

359
00:11:16,571 --> 00:11:17,683
a club, a history.

360
00:11:17,749 --> 00:11:20,095
The profiles were detailed, confident,

361
00:11:20,162 --> 00:11:21,643
and completely invented.

362
00:11:21,710 --> 00:11:23,438
And they worked — because no

363
00:11:23,505 --> 00:11:25,665
one downstream was looking closely.

364
00:11:25,732 --> 00:11:27,584
The coach had already vouched.

365
00:11:27,650 --> 00:11:29,441
The whole system runs on that

366
00:11:29,507 --> 00:11:31,297
trust, and the trust had been

367
00:11:31,364 --> 00:11:32,364
bought.

368
00:11:32,431 --> 00:11:34,406
And the athletic machine had one

369
00:11:34,473 --> 00:11:36,695
advantage over the testing machine —

370
00:11:36,762 --> 00:11:38,675
it scaled. Rigging a test meant

371
00:11:38,742 --> 00:11:41,087
flying Riddell in, controlling a room,

372
00:11:41,154 --> 00:11:42,944
threading a believable score.

373
00:11:43,011 --> 00:11:44,863
But a fake recruit needed only

374
00:11:44,929 --> 00:11:46,905
a willing coach and a convincing

375
00:11:46,971 --> 00:11:48,885
folder. Once you had an insider

376
00:11:48,952 --> 00:11:50,865
who would vouch, you could push

377
00:11:50,932 --> 00:11:53,031
child after child through the same

378
00:11:53,097 --> 00:11:54,764
door, year after year — and

379
00:11:54,831 --> 00:11:56,929
from the outside it looked exactly

380
00:11:56,996 --> 00:11:59,218
like a talented kid being recruited.

381
00:11:59,285 --> 00:12:01,075
The fraud hid inside the most

382
00:12:01,142 --> 00:12:03,549
ordinary thing a university does: trust

383
00:12:03,616 --> 00:12:04,616
its own people.

384
00:12:06,549 --> 00:12:08,524
Then Singer delivered the bribe,

385
00:12:08,591 --> 00:12:10,813
and a corrupt coach or administrator

386
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:12,793
waved the fake recruit through.

387
00:12:12,860 --> 00:12:15,082
The scheme reached coaches and staff

388
00:12:15,149 --> 00:12:17,186
named in the case at universities

389
00:12:17,253 --> 00:12:19,228
most families only dream about —

390
00:12:19,295 --> 00:12:21,887
Yale, Stanford, the University of Southern

391
00:12:21,954 --> 00:12:24,176
California, Georgetown, Wake Forest,

392
00:12:24,243 --> 00:12:26,342
U.C.L.A., the University of Texas.

393
00:12:26,408 --> 00:12:28,137
At U.S.C., one of the people

394
00:12:28,203 --> 00:12:29,808
on the inside was a senior

395
00:12:29,875 --> 00:12:32,282
associate athletic director named Donna

396
00:12:32,349 --> 00:12:34,880
Heinel. Prosecutors said she helped usher

397
00:12:34,947 --> 00:12:36,860
fake recruits through the door,

398
00:12:36,927 --> 00:12:39,026
taking more than a million dollars

399
00:12:39,092 --> 00:12:41,561
into university accounts she controlled,

400
00:12:41,628 --> 00:12:43,480
plus about a hundred and sixty

401
00:12:43,547 --> 00:12:45,830
thousand dollars for her own benefit.

402
00:12:45,897 --> 00:12:48,181
She pleaded guilty to honest-services

403
00:12:48,248 --> 00:12:50,161
fraud, and was sentenced to six

404
00:12:50,228 --> 00:12:52,203
months. She was the gatekeeper —

405
00:12:52,270 --> 00:12:54,554
the trusted insider who decided which

406
00:12:54,621 --> 00:12:55,855
names moved forward.

407
00:12:55,922 --> 00:12:57,589
And her trust was for sale.

408
00:12:57,655 --> 00:12:59,198
Which is the moment to be

409
00:12:59,265 --> 00:13:01,302
very precise about who the victim

410
00:13:01,369 --> 00:13:03,714
is. The universities were not charged.

411
00:13:03,781 --> 00:13:06,374
Prosecutors treated the schools themselves

412
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:07,984
as victims of the fraud —

413
00:13:08,050 --> 00:13:10,272
because the people taking the bribes

414
00:13:10,339 --> 00:13:12,314
were the schools' own employees,

415
00:13:12,381 --> 00:13:14,850
betraying the institutions that paid and

416
00:13:14,917 --> 00:13:16,275
trusted them. The U.S.

417
00:13:16,342 --> 00:13:18,564
Attorney said it flatly: the schools

418
00:13:18,630 --> 00:13:20,297
themselves are not targets.

419
00:13:20,364 --> 00:13:21,537
Two machines, then.

420
00:13:21,603 --> 00:13:23,517
One rigged the great equalizer.

421
00:13:23,584 --> 00:13:25,435
The other forged a talent that

422
00:13:25,502 --> 00:13:27,971
never existed. Together, they could move

423
00:13:28,038 --> 00:13:29,828
almost any child to the front

424
00:13:29,895 --> 00:13:31,314
of almost any line — as

425
00:13:31,381 --> 00:13:33,233
long as the parents could pay.

426
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:34,781
And these parents could.

427
00:13:34,848 --> 00:13:36,329
So who buys a guarantee?

428
00:13:36,396 --> 00:13:38,248
When the case broke, two names

429
00:13:38,314 --> 00:13:40,290
pulled all the light toward them

430
00:13:40,356 --> 00:13:42,579
— because America already knew their

431
00:13:42,645 --> 00:13:44,003
faces from television.

432
00:13:44,070 --> 00:13:46,169
The first was the actress Felicity

433
00:13:46,235 --> 00:13:48,828
Huffman. Prosecutors said she paid fifteen

434
00:13:48,895 --> 00:13:50,993
thousand dollars to have a proctor

435
00:13:51,060 --> 00:13:53,591
secretly correct her older daughter's SAT

436
00:13:53,658 --> 00:13:55,633
answers after the test was over.

437
00:13:55,700 --> 00:13:57,551
She pleaded guilty to a single

438
00:13:57,618 --> 00:13:59,223
count of fraud conspiracy.

439
00:13:59,290 --> 00:14:01,203
And she became the first parent

440
00:14:01,270 --> 00:14:02,751
in the entire case to be

441
00:14:02,818 --> 00:14:04,732
sentenced — to fourteen days in

442
00:14:04,798 --> 00:14:07,391
prison, a thirty-thousand-dollar fine, and

443
00:14:07,458 --> 00:14:08,569
community service.

444
00:14:08,635 --> 00:14:10,796
Fourteen days. To some, that number

445
00:14:10,863 --> 00:14:13,085
proved the system still bends gently

446
00:14:13,151 --> 00:14:14,756
for the powerful — a slap,

447
00:14:14,823 --> 00:14:16,490
a long weekend, a headline.

448
00:14:16,556 --> 00:14:18,470
To others, it was startling for

449
00:14:18,537 --> 00:14:20,389
the opposite reason: a famous,

450
00:14:20,455 --> 00:14:22,677
wealthy parent had actually been put

451
00:14:22,744 --> 00:14:24,226
in a cell for buying her

452
00:14:24,292 --> 00:14:25,292
child an edge.

453
00:14:25,359 --> 00:14:26,902
Both reactions were fair.

454
00:14:26,969 --> 00:14:28,759
And that tension — too harsh,

455
00:14:28,826 --> 00:14:30,245
or far too soft — would

456
00:14:30,312 --> 00:14:32,658
shadow every sentence that came after.

457
00:14:32,724 --> 00:14:34,391
The second name was bigger.

458
00:14:34,458 --> 00:14:36,865
The actress Lori Loughlin, beloved from

459
00:14:36,932 --> 00:14:39,030
a wholesome family sitcom, and her

460
00:14:39,097 --> 00:14:41,381
husband, the fashion designer Mossimo

461
00:14:41,448 --> 00:14:43,793
Giannulli. Prosecutors said the couple

462
00:14:43,860 --> 00:14:46,082
paid five hundred thousand dollars —

463
00:14:46,149 --> 00:14:47,630
half a million — to have

464
00:14:47,697 --> 00:14:50,105
their two daughters labeled as recruits

465
00:14:50,171 --> 00:14:51,591
to the crew team at the

466
00:14:51,658 --> 00:14:53,756
University of Southern California.

467
00:14:53,823 --> 00:14:56,107
Neither daughter rowed competitively.

468
00:14:56,174 --> 00:14:58,087
The file even included a staged

469
00:14:58,154 --> 00:15:00,068
photograph on an ergometer — an

470
00:15:00,134 --> 00:15:01,492
indoor rowing machine.

471
00:15:01,559 --> 00:15:03,226
And here the wording has to

472
00:15:03,292 --> 00:15:05,082
be exact, because this is the

473
00:15:05,149 --> 00:15:07,124
case most people remember wrong.

474
00:15:07,191 --> 00:15:09,537
Loughlin and Giannulli did not quietly

475
00:15:09,603 --> 00:15:11,826
fold. They first pleaded not guilty,

476
00:15:11,892 --> 00:15:13,868
and fought the charges for about

477
00:15:13,934 --> 00:15:15,601
a year. Then they reversed,

478
00:15:15,668 --> 00:15:17,458
and pleaded guilty — but only

479
00:15:17,524 --> 00:15:18,759
to fraud conspiracy.

480
00:15:18,826 --> 00:15:20,801
The more serious counts that had

481
00:15:20,868 --> 00:15:23,398
been added against them, money laundering

482
00:15:23,465 --> 00:15:25,626
and bribery, were dismissed as part

483
00:15:25,692 --> 00:15:26,692
of the deal.

484
00:15:26,759 --> 00:15:28,796
They were not convicted of those.

485
00:15:28,863 --> 00:15:31,085
Loughlin was sentenced to two months

486
00:15:31,151 --> 00:15:33,003
in prison. Giannulli, to five.

487
00:15:33,070 --> 00:15:34,860
But the two famous faces were

488
00:15:34,927 --> 00:15:36,717
never really the story — they

489
00:15:36,784 --> 00:15:38,635
were just the ones the cameras

490
00:15:38,702 --> 00:15:41,048
already knew. Behind them stood dozens

491
00:15:41,114 --> 00:15:43,151
more parents: in the initial case

492
00:15:43,218 --> 00:15:44,947
alone, thirty-three of them.

493
00:15:45,013 --> 00:15:47,482
Business leaders, lawyers, financiers, a

494
00:15:47,549 --> 00:15:49,771
vineyard owner, a casino executive —

495
00:15:49,838 --> 00:15:52,430
people accustomed to solving problems with

496
00:15:52,497 --> 00:15:54,596
money, who had simply pointed that

497
00:15:54,663 --> 00:15:56,761
habit at their children's futures.

498
00:15:56,828 --> 00:15:58,927
Strip away the celebrity, and what

499
00:15:58,993 --> 00:16:00,475
is left is a portrait of

500
00:16:00,542 --> 00:16:02,517
a class that had quietly decided

501
00:16:02,584 --> 00:16:04,621
the ordinary rules were for other

502
00:16:04,687 --> 00:16:05,687
people.

503
00:16:05,754 --> 00:16:07,853
And picture what that staged photo

504
00:16:07,919 --> 00:16:10,450
actually required. A parent, posing their

505
00:16:10,517 --> 00:16:11,937
own child for a fraud —

506
00:16:12,003 --> 00:16:13,732
telling them to climb onto a

507
00:16:13,798 --> 00:16:15,959
rowing machine they had never used,

508
00:16:16,026 --> 00:16:17,569
to grip it a certain way,

509
00:16:17,635 --> 00:16:19,055
to look the part, for a

510
00:16:19,122 --> 00:16:20,850
sport they would never play,

511
00:16:20,917 --> 00:16:22,398
at a school they had not

512
00:16:22,465 --> 00:16:24,502
earned. Whatever the parents told

513
00:16:24,569 --> 00:16:26,729
themselves, that was the moment the

514
00:16:26,796 --> 00:16:28,524
lie became a family project.

515
00:16:28,591 --> 00:16:30,319
The child was no longer just

516
00:16:30,386 --> 00:16:32,670
being helped. They were being written

517
00:16:32,737 --> 00:16:33,737
into the script.

518
00:16:33,803 --> 00:16:35,285
It would be easy to turn

519
00:16:35,351 --> 00:16:37,574
these parents into cartoon villains.

520
00:16:37,640 --> 00:16:39,863
But the truth is more uncomfortable,

521
00:16:39,929 --> 00:16:41,966
because the want underneath it is

522
00:16:42,033 --> 00:16:43,391
so painfully ordinary.

523
00:16:43,458 --> 00:16:44,816
They loved their kids.

524
00:16:44,882 --> 00:16:47,043
They wanted them safe, and settled,

525
00:16:47,109 --> 00:16:48,714
and proud — wanted to hand

526
00:16:48,781 --> 00:16:50,633
them the future the family had

527
00:16:50,700 --> 00:16:53,292
always pictured. Almost every parent feels

528
00:16:53,359 --> 00:16:54,964
some version of that pull.

529
00:16:55,030 --> 00:16:57,191
The corruption was never in wanting

530
00:16:57,258 --> 00:16:58,739
the best for your child.

531
00:16:58,806 --> 00:17:00,534
It was in deciding that your

532
00:17:00,601 --> 00:17:02,638
money entitled you to simply take

533
00:17:02,705 --> 00:17:04,186
it — even when taking it

534
00:17:04,253 --> 00:17:06,351
meant taking it from someone else.

535
00:17:06,418 --> 00:17:08,208
Because that is the part this

536
00:17:08,275 --> 00:17:10,127
scandal forces into the light.

537
00:17:10,193 --> 00:17:12,107
Elite admission is not a faucet

538
00:17:12,174 --> 00:17:13,902
that runs faster if you push

539
00:17:13,969 --> 00:17:15,697
harder. It is a fixed number

540
00:17:15,764 --> 00:17:17,677
of seats. Every single place is

541
00:17:17,744 --> 00:17:18,917
a chair, in a room,

542
00:17:18,984 --> 00:17:20,712
behind a locked door, with a

543
00:17:20,779 --> 00:17:22,384
long line waiting outside.

544
00:17:22,450 --> 00:17:23,870
So when a fake rower is

545
00:17:23,937 --> 00:17:25,603
waved inside, a real one is

546
00:17:25,670 --> 00:17:27,707
waved away. When a corrected test

547
00:17:27,774 --> 00:17:29,687
score jumps the line, an honest

548
00:17:29,754 --> 00:17:31,606
score quietly slips behind it.

549
00:17:31,672 --> 00:17:33,339
The U.S. Attorney put it in

550
00:17:33,406 --> 00:17:35,505
one sentence that cut cleaner than

551
00:17:35,571 --> 00:17:37,917
any charge: for every student admitted

552
00:17:37,984 --> 00:17:40,144
through fraud, an honest, genuinely

553
00:17:40,211 --> 00:17:42,063
talented student was rejected.

554
00:17:42,129 --> 00:17:43,426
Picture that student.

555
00:17:43,492 --> 00:17:45,282
They never saw the side door.

556
00:17:45,349 --> 00:17:47,139
Never even knew it was there.

557
00:17:47,206 --> 00:17:49,551
They just received a thinner envelope,

558
00:17:49,618 --> 00:17:51,161
and carried away a quiet,

559
00:17:51,228 --> 00:17:53,635
lifelong suspicion that they simply had

560
00:17:53,702 --> 00:17:55,369
not been good enough — when

561
00:17:55,435 --> 00:17:57,349
the truth was that someone with

562
00:17:57,416 --> 00:17:59,206
more money had been standing,

563
00:17:59,272 --> 00:18:01,371
invisibly, exactly where they were

564
00:18:01,438 --> 00:18:02,438
supposed to be.

565
00:18:02,505 --> 00:18:04,171
This is why the scandal cut

566
00:18:04,238 --> 00:18:06,090
so much deeper than the people

567
00:18:06,156 --> 00:18:08,008
charged. Most of us are raised

568
00:18:08,075 --> 00:18:09,989
on a single promise: work hard,

569
00:18:10,055 --> 00:18:11,660
earn it, and the door will

570
00:18:11,727 --> 00:18:13,579
open. That promise is the deal

571
00:18:13,645 --> 00:18:15,744
that makes the whole long struggle

572
00:18:15,811 --> 00:18:16,811
feel worth it.

573
00:18:16,877 --> 00:18:19,470
Operation Varsity Blues showed millions of

574
00:18:19,537 --> 00:18:21,203
people, in black and white,

575
00:18:21,270 --> 00:18:23,184
that for some families the door

576
00:18:23,250 --> 00:18:24,793
had a price, the line was

577
00:18:24,860 --> 00:18:26,897
shorter, and the promise they had

578
00:18:26,964 --> 00:18:29,124
built their lives around carried an

579
00:18:29,191 --> 00:18:31,105
asterisk they were never shown.

580
00:18:31,171 --> 00:18:32,961
And yet — not everyone inside

581
00:18:33,028 --> 00:18:34,263
the scheme got rich.

582
00:18:34,329 --> 00:18:36,737
That nuance matters, because it refuses

583
00:18:36,803 --> 00:18:38,593
to let the story stay simple.

584
00:18:38,660 --> 00:18:40,635
The Stanford sailing coach, John

585
00:18:40,702 --> 00:18:42,307
Vandemoer, pleaded guilty.

586
00:18:42,374 --> 00:18:44,040
But the six hundred and ten

587
00:18:44,107 --> 00:18:46,329
thousand dollars he accepted did not

588
00:18:46,396 --> 00:18:47,816
go into his own pocket.

589
00:18:47,882 --> 00:18:49,858
It went into the sailing program

590
00:18:49,924 --> 00:18:51,282
he ran — better boats,

591
00:18:51,349 --> 00:18:52,349
a stronger team.

592
00:18:52,416 --> 00:18:54,268
The judge called him the least

593
00:18:54,334 --> 00:18:56,495
culpable person in the entire case,

594
00:18:56,561 --> 00:18:58,351
and sentenced him to a single

595
00:18:58,418 --> 00:19:00,332
day, already considered served.

596
00:19:00,398 --> 00:19:02,250
Hold those people side by side

597
00:19:02,317 --> 00:19:03,317
for a moment.

598
00:19:03,384 --> 00:19:05,482
One coach traded his integrity and

599
00:19:05,549 --> 00:19:07,092
kept nothing for himself.

600
00:19:07,159 --> 00:19:09,505
Parents traded their integrity to keep

601
00:19:09,571 --> 00:19:11,423
everything for their children.

602
00:19:11,490 --> 00:19:13,218
The fixer in the middle kept

603
00:19:13,285 --> 00:19:15,137
the difference — the millions.

604
00:19:15,203 --> 00:19:16,808
And the only people in the

605
00:19:16,875 --> 00:19:18,974
whole story with truly clean hands

606
00:19:19,040 --> 00:19:20,707
were the ones who never got

607
00:19:20,774 --> 00:19:22,440
the call, and never got the

608
00:19:22,507 --> 00:19:23,507
seat.

609
00:19:23,574 --> 00:19:25,426
And here is the cruelty buried

610
00:19:25,492 --> 00:19:26,492
in the math.

611
00:19:26,559 --> 00:19:28,596
The students who lost their seats

612
00:19:28,663 --> 00:19:30,268
will almost never know it.

613
00:19:30,334 --> 00:19:32,063
There is no letter that says

614
00:19:32,129 --> 00:19:33,981
you were displaced by a bribe.

615
00:19:34,048 --> 00:19:36,208
The harm is invisible, untraceable,

616
00:19:36,275 --> 00:19:38,744
spread thin across thousands of ordinary

617
00:19:38,811 --> 00:19:40,848
rejections — which is exactly why

618
00:19:40,914 --> 00:19:42,519
a scheme like this can run

619
00:19:42,586 --> 00:19:44,561
for years before anyone notices.

620
00:19:44,628 --> 00:19:46,480
The victims are real, and they

621
00:19:46,547 --> 00:19:48,398
are everywhere, and not one of

622
00:19:48,465 --> 00:19:50,193
them can point to the moment

623
00:19:50,260 --> 00:19:51,495
it happened to them.

624
00:19:51,561 --> 00:19:53,166
So how does a machine this

625
00:19:53,233 --> 00:19:55,147
profitable, this discreet, this

626
00:19:55,213 --> 00:19:57,065
well-disguised, finally break?

627
00:19:57,132 --> 00:19:58,551
Not through admissions.

628
00:19:58,618 --> 00:20:00,840
Through an accident, in a completely

629
00:20:00,907 --> 00:20:03,314
different investigation. Federal agents

630
00:20:03,381 --> 00:20:05,542
working an unrelated case were told

631
00:20:05,608 --> 00:20:07,028
— by a target trying to

632
00:20:07,095 --> 00:20:08,823
help himself — about a coach

633
00:20:08,890 --> 00:20:10,618
at Yale who would take money

634
00:20:10,685 --> 00:20:12,598
to call an applicant a recruit.

635
00:20:12,665 --> 00:20:14,455
That coach was Rudy Meredith,

636
00:20:14,522 --> 00:20:16,374
the head women's soccer coach,

637
00:20:16,440 --> 00:20:18,724
who had accepted around eight hundred

638
00:20:18,791 --> 00:20:20,458
and sixty thousand dollars.

639
00:20:20,524 --> 00:20:22,870
Cornered, Meredith began to cooperate.

640
00:20:22,937 --> 00:20:24,665
And in one recorded meeting,

641
00:20:24,732 --> 00:20:26,213
he gave the agents a far

642
00:20:26,280 --> 00:20:27,514
bigger name. Singer.

643
00:20:27,581 --> 00:20:29,556
Once they had Singer, the entire

644
00:20:29,623 --> 00:20:31,660
architecture lit up — because the

645
00:20:31,727 --> 00:20:34,072
architect himself agreed to cooperate.

646
00:20:34,139 --> 00:20:36,114
He began recording his own phone

647
00:20:36,181 --> 00:20:37,909
calls, with his own clients,

648
00:20:37,976 --> 00:20:40,075
the parents, who talked openly and

649
00:20:40,142 --> 00:20:42,117
comfortably about the side door,

650
00:20:42,184 --> 00:20:44,406
not knowing that federal agents were

651
00:20:44,472 --> 00:20:46,139
listening on the other end.

652
00:20:46,206 --> 00:20:48,243
The salesman had become the wire.

653
00:20:48,309 --> 00:20:49,914
It is worth pausing on how

654
00:20:49,981 --> 00:20:51,524
strange that reversal is.

655
00:20:51,591 --> 00:20:53,998
For years, Singer's entire business had

656
00:20:54,065 --> 00:20:56,226
depended on discretion — on parents

657
00:20:56,292 --> 00:20:58,391
trusting that he would never talk.

658
00:20:58,458 --> 00:21:00,742
Now the government's case depended on

659
00:21:00,808 --> 00:21:03,092
him talking constantly, into a phone,

660
00:21:03,159 --> 00:21:05,072
while they recorded every word.

661
00:21:05,139 --> 00:21:06,991
The same charm that had closed

662
00:21:07,058 --> 00:21:08,909
every deal was now closing the

663
00:21:08,976 --> 00:21:11,260
trap. Some parents, prosecutors said,

664
00:21:11,327 --> 00:21:13,117
were caught on those calls in

665
00:21:13,184 --> 00:21:14,974
the very act of arranging the

666
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:16,151
next year's fraud.

667
00:21:16,218 --> 00:21:18,255
Those recordings are the spine of

668
00:21:18,322 --> 00:21:20,668
the case. The smooth, reassuring voice

669
00:21:20,734 --> 00:21:22,586
on the line, walking a nervous

670
00:21:22,653 --> 00:21:25,060
parent through the plan, soothing them,

671
00:21:25,127 --> 00:21:27,411
promising the guarantee — while every

672
00:21:27,477 --> 00:21:29,453
word fed straight into a federal

673
00:21:29,519 --> 00:21:31,803
file. Everything that had made Singer

674
00:21:31,870 --> 00:21:33,351
good at the scheme — the

675
00:21:33,418 --> 00:21:35,332
calm, the certainty, the talk —

676
00:21:35,398 --> 00:21:37,312
was now the evidence that would

677
00:21:37,379 --> 00:21:38,379
end it.

678
00:21:38,445 --> 00:21:39,803
Then came the morning.

679
00:21:39,870 --> 00:21:41,105
March twelfth, 2019.

680
00:21:41,171 --> 00:21:43,764
In coordinated arrests across the country,

681
00:21:43,830 --> 00:21:46,423
prosecutors in Boston unsealed the charges

682
00:21:46,490 --> 00:21:48,589
and took fifty people into custody

683
00:21:48,655 --> 00:21:50,322
at once — parents, coaches,

684
00:21:50,389 --> 00:21:52,364
administrators, the test-fixers.

685
00:21:52,430 --> 00:21:54,468
And they gave the investigation a

686
00:21:54,534 --> 00:21:56,571
name that would outlive every one

687
00:21:56,638 --> 00:21:58,675
of them: Operation Varsity Blues.

688
00:21:58,742 --> 00:22:00,100
For a few days, it was

689
00:22:00,166 --> 00:22:01,771
the only story in America.

690
00:22:01,838 --> 00:22:04,307
Not because corruption in admissions was

691
00:22:04,374 --> 00:22:06,102
new — but because, for once,

692
00:22:06,169 --> 00:22:08,206
it had names everyone recognized,

693
00:22:08,272 --> 00:22:10,495
a price tag attached, and recordings

694
00:22:10,561 --> 00:22:12,537
of the powerful saying the quiet

695
00:22:12,603 --> 00:22:13,603
part out loud.

696
00:22:13,670 --> 00:22:15,460
And the spectacle was part of

697
00:22:15,527 --> 00:22:17,811
the point. For decades, the advantage

698
00:22:17,877 --> 00:22:19,668
of the rich in admissions had

699
00:22:19,734 --> 00:22:21,709
been an open secret — discussed,

700
00:22:21,776 --> 00:22:23,937
resented, but never quite provable.

701
00:22:24,003 --> 00:22:25,855
Now there were court dates and

702
00:22:25,922 --> 00:22:28,329
famous defendants walking past cameras.

703
00:22:28,396 --> 00:22:30,001
The country got to watch a

704
00:22:30,068 --> 00:22:32,043
piece of the tilt finally answer

705
00:22:32,109 --> 00:22:33,714
for itself in a courtroom.

706
00:22:33,781 --> 00:22:34,892
It was satisfying.

707
00:22:34,959 --> 00:22:36,317
It was also, in a way,

708
00:22:36,384 --> 00:22:38,606
a distraction — because the loudest,

709
00:22:38,672 --> 00:22:40,895
most criminal sliver was the easiest

710
00:22:40,961 --> 00:22:41,961
part to punish.

711
00:22:43,277 --> 00:22:45,314
The reckoning itself came slowly,

712
00:22:45,381 --> 00:22:47,047
in pieces, over years — one

713
00:22:47,114 --> 00:22:48,410
sentencing at a time.

714
00:22:48,477 --> 00:22:50,761
Mark Riddell, the test-taker, pleaded

715
00:22:50,828 --> 00:22:52,803
guilty and was sentenced to four

716
00:22:52,870 --> 00:22:54,845
months. Donna Heinel, the U.S.C.

717
00:22:54,912 --> 00:22:55,912
insider, to six.

718
00:22:55,978 --> 00:22:58,139
Rudy Meredith, the Yale coach whose

719
00:22:58,205 --> 00:23:00,675
cooperation cracked it open, was himself

720
00:23:00,741 --> 00:23:02,902
sentenced, in 2022, to five months.

721
00:23:02,968 --> 00:23:04,697
One by one, the parents were

722
00:23:04,763 --> 00:23:05,763
sentenced too.

723
00:23:07,985 --> 00:23:10,392
Their sentences were mostly measured in

724
00:23:10,459 --> 00:23:12,249
weeks and months, not years —

725
00:23:12,316 --> 00:23:14,662
fines, short stays, community service.

726
00:23:14,728 --> 00:23:16,704
To critics, that was the scandal

727
00:23:16,770 --> 00:23:18,684
after the scandal: even caught,

728
00:23:18,750 --> 00:23:20,973
even on tape, the punishments stayed

729
00:23:21,039 --> 00:23:23,200
small. But the more lasting penalty

730
00:23:23,266 --> 00:23:24,871
was never the prison term.

731
00:23:24,938 --> 00:23:26,543
It was the public record —

732
00:23:26,610 --> 00:23:28,585
people who had spent their whole

733
00:23:28,652 --> 00:23:31,121
lives buying their way past consequences

734
00:23:31,187 --> 00:23:33,471
now had a federal conviction attached

735
00:23:33,538 --> 00:23:35,884
to their name, permanently, for anyone

736
00:23:35,950 --> 00:23:36,950
to see.

737
00:23:37,017 --> 00:23:38,684
And Singer — the architect,

738
00:23:38,750 --> 00:23:40,479
the salesman, the man in the

739
00:23:40,545 --> 00:23:42,644
doorway. He pleaded guilty to four

740
00:23:42,711 --> 00:23:45,180
federal felonies, including racketeering

741
00:23:45,247 --> 00:23:46,543
and money laundering.

742
00:23:46,610 --> 00:23:48,523
In January of 2023, nearly four

743
00:23:48,590 --> 00:23:50,504
years after the arrests, he was

744
00:23:50,570 --> 00:23:52,360
sentenced to three and a half

745
00:23:52,427 --> 00:23:54,341
years in prison, and ordered to

746
00:23:54,407 --> 00:23:56,444
pay more than ten million dollars

747
00:23:56,511 --> 00:23:58,239
in restitution to the I.R.S.

748
00:23:58,306 --> 00:24:00,096
— the exact taxes his clients

749
00:24:00,163 --> 00:24:02,323
had dodged through that fake little

750
00:24:02,390 --> 00:24:03,390
charity.

751
00:24:03,457 --> 00:24:05,185
By the time the case finally

752
00:24:05,252 --> 00:24:07,350
closed, fifty-five people had been

753
00:24:07,417 --> 00:24:09,948
charged, and fifty-three were convicted —

754
00:24:10,015 --> 00:24:11,496
almost none of them by a

755
00:24:11,563 --> 00:24:13,229
jury. Almost all of them by

756
00:24:13,296 --> 00:24:14,654
their own guilty plea.

757
00:24:14,721 --> 00:24:16,573
Because there was, in the end,

758
00:24:16,639 --> 00:24:18,615
very little left to argue about.

759
00:24:18,681 --> 00:24:20,595
The recordings had already said

760
00:24:20,662 --> 00:24:21,662
everything.

761
00:24:21,728 --> 00:24:23,889
And then, slowly, the country moved

762
00:24:23,955 --> 00:24:25,252
on — which is its own

763
00:24:25,318 --> 00:24:26,318
kind of ending.

764
00:24:26,385 --> 00:24:28,360
A few schools tightened how they

765
00:24:28,427 --> 00:24:30,773
verify recruits. The testing companies

766
00:24:30,839 --> 00:24:32,691
faced uncomfortable questions.

767
00:24:32,758 --> 00:24:35,042
But the deeper machinery of advantage

768
00:24:35,108 --> 00:24:37,022
— the elite tutors, the private

769
00:24:37,089 --> 00:24:39,373
consultants, the legal donations, the

770
00:24:39,439 --> 00:24:41,538
family connections — kept running,

771
00:24:41,605 --> 00:24:43,580
perfectly legal, in plain sight.

772
00:24:43,647 --> 00:24:46,239
The scandal removed one criminal shortcut.

773
00:24:46,306 --> 00:24:48,220
It never touched the highway it

774
00:24:48,286 --> 00:24:49,286
sat beside.

775
00:24:49,647 --> 00:24:51,375
And notice what else did not

776
00:24:51,442 --> 00:24:53,911
happen. No university lost its standing.

777
00:24:53,978 --> 00:24:55,459
No diploma was recalled.

778
00:24:55,526 --> 00:24:57,872
The buildings still carry the engraved

779
00:24:57,938 --> 00:24:59,852
names of back-door donors — the

780
00:24:59,919 --> 00:25:02,141
families who gave their fortunes the

781
00:25:02,207 --> 00:25:04,121
legal way, and were thanked for

782
00:25:04,188 --> 00:25:05,978
it. The side door was quietly

783
00:25:06,045 --> 00:25:08,205
bricked up. And the larger question

784
00:25:08,272 --> 00:25:10,247
it had exposed was left standing

785
00:25:10,314 --> 00:25:11,314
wide open.

786
00:25:11,380 --> 00:25:13,047
In the end, Rick Singer did

787
00:25:13,114 --> 00:25:15,274
not invent the advantage that money

788
00:25:15,341 --> 00:25:16,341
buys at the top.

789
00:25:16,407 --> 00:25:18,259
He simply sold the most honest

790
00:25:18,326 --> 00:25:20,054
version of a lie that almost

791
00:25:20,121 --> 00:25:22,714
everyone already half-believed — that with

792
00:25:22,780 --> 00:25:24,694
enough money, the rules soften,

793
00:25:24,761 --> 00:25:26,489
the line shifts, and a place

794
00:25:26,556 --> 00:25:28,346
that is supposed to be earned

795
00:25:28,412 --> 00:25:29,770
can just be purchased.

796
00:25:29,837 --> 00:25:31,380
His real crime, in a way,

797
00:25:31,447 --> 00:25:33,731
was not understanding that the system

798
00:25:33,798 --> 00:25:35,773
rewards wealth. Plenty of people

799
00:25:35,840 --> 00:25:38,185
understand that. His crime was turning

800
00:25:38,252 --> 00:25:39,733
it into a product — with

801
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:41,096
a menu, a price list,

802
00:25:41,163 --> 00:25:42,768
and a guarantee — and then

803
00:25:42,835 --> 00:25:44,810
getting caught putting all of it

804
00:25:44,877 --> 00:25:45,877
on tape.

805
00:25:45,943 --> 00:25:47,548
And that is why this story

806
00:25:47,615 --> 00:25:49,158
refuses to feel finished.

807
00:25:49,225 --> 00:25:51,200
The front door is still crowded.

808
00:25:51,267 --> 00:25:52,995
The back door is still open,

809
00:25:53,062 --> 00:25:54,852
and still perfectly legal — a

810
00:25:54,919 --> 00:25:57,017
large enough fortune can still buy

811
00:25:57,084 --> 00:25:59,121
your child a longer, warmer look,

812
00:25:59,188 --> 00:26:00,607
and no one will ever be

813
00:26:00,674 --> 00:26:01,674
arrested for it.

814
00:26:01,741 --> 00:26:04,025
Singer only fell because his shortcut

815
00:26:04,091 --> 00:26:05,820
crossed a line the law could

816
00:26:05,887 --> 00:26:07,924
name. The deeper unfairness — the

817
00:26:07,990 --> 00:26:09,780
kind that was legal the whole

818
00:26:09,847 --> 00:26:11,452
time — simply walked away,

819
00:26:11,519 --> 00:26:13,556
untouched, and went back to work.

820
00:26:13,622 --> 00:26:15,474
Maybe that is the quiet lesson

821
00:26:15,541 --> 00:26:17,022
hiding inside all of it.

822
00:26:17,089 --> 00:26:19,064
The greatest damage was not done

823
00:26:19,131 --> 00:26:21,106
by the loud, criminal fraud that

824
00:26:21,173 --> 00:26:22,346
made the headlines.

825
00:26:22,412 --> 00:26:24,388
It was done by everything around

826
00:26:24,454 --> 00:26:26,059
it that stayed legal — the

827
00:26:26,126 --> 00:26:28,719
steady, invisible advantage that never has

828
00:26:28,785 --> 00:26:30,452
to knock, because for some,

829
00:26:30,519 --> 00:26:32,494
the door was simply always open.

830
00:26:32,561 --> 00:26:34,104
The crime was the part we

831
00:26:34,170 --> 00:26:36,207
could see. The unfairness was the

832
00:26:36,274 --> 00:26:37,632
part we agreed not to.

833
00:26:37,699 --> 00:26:39,242
So the next time you hear

834
00:26:39,309 --> 00:26:41,469
that someone got in, somewhere that

835
00:26:41,536 --> 00:26:43,635
felt impossible, and a small voice

836
00:26:43,701 --> 00:26:44,936
in you asks how — do

837
00:26:45,003 --> 00:26:46,422
not rush to silence it.

838
00:26:46,489 --> 00:26:47,847
Sit with the question.

839
00:26:47,914 --> 00:26:50,506
Because the most important thing Operation

840
00:26:50,573 --> 00:26:52,857
Varsity Blues revealed was never that

841
00:26:52,924 --> 00:26:54,714
a few famous parents cheated.

842
00:26:54,780 --> 00:26:56,817
It was that somewhere, an honest,

843
00:26:56,884 --> 00:26:59,477
talented student received a rejection they

844
00:26:59,543 --> 00:27:00,963
did not earn — and went

845
00:27:01,030 --> 00:27:03,190
their whole life never knowing why.

846
00:27:03,257 --> 00:27:04,800
So before the last word —

847
00:27:04,867 --> 00:27:06,348
if you believe a seat at

848
00:27:06,415 --> 00:27:07,958
the top should be earned,

849
00:27:08,025 --> 00:27:09,815
not bought, then do the small

850
00:27:09,882 --> 00:27:12,166
honest thing this whole story refused

851
00:27:12,232 --> 00:27:14,146
to do. Tap like, and subscribe.

852
00:27:14,212 --> 00:27:15,879
It takes a second, it costs

853
00:27:15,946 --> 00:27:17,366
you nothing — and it is

854
00:27:17,432 --> 00:27:19,161
the one vote here that money

855
00:27:19,227 --> 00:27:20,227
cannot rig.

856
00:27:20,294 --> 00:27:22,393
Because somewhere out there is the

857
00:27:22,459 --> 00:27:24,311
student who was turned away to

858
00:27:24,378 --> 00:27:25,983
make room. This one is for

859
00:27:26,049 --> 00:27:27,778
them. Stay with us — because

860
00:27:27,845 --> 00:27:29,758
next time, we open another door

861
00:27:29,825 --> 00:27:31,862
that was never supposed to exist.
